# Nginx Module#

## Overview ##

This is a module for installing and configuring nginx.

The 'nginx' Class performs system-wide installation.

Defines are used to create vhost/application configurations.

APP TYPE  Define                 App Overview
---------------------------------------------------------
STATIC    'ngapp::static'    HTTP Static files 
PHP       'ngapp::php'       PHP app using PHP-FPM 
PASSENGER 'ngapp::passenger' Ruby/Rack apps using Passenger-Standalone 
UNICORN   'ngapp::unicorn'   Ruby/Rack apps using Unicorn 

## Usage ##

To use:
- run the 'nginx' Class once per server
- create & config a user account using 'ngusr'
- run the appropriate 'ngvac::*' Define once per app

Sample Usage :

        include nginx
        
        ngusr { 'deploy' : } 

        ngapp::php { "default" :
          root         => "/var/www/nginx-default",
          fastcgi_pass => "127.0.0.1:9000",
          server_name  => ["localhost", "$hostname", "$fqdn"],
         }

        ngapp::passenger { "default-ssl" :
          listen       => "443",
          root         => "/var/www/nginx-default",
          fastcgi_pass => "127.0.0.1:9000",
          server_name  => "$fqdn",
        }

See the test setups for more usage examples.
